{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"41306","heading":"Report to Congress on banking law offenses","label":"41306 Report to Congress on banking law offenses","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/stIV/ch413","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","CodificationSection was formerly classified as a note under , Judiciary and Judicial Procedure, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.section 522 of Title 28"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"In general","label":"a In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Data collection","label":"1 Data collection","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fa%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the nature and number of civil and criminal investigations, prosecutions, and related proceedings, and civil enforcement and recovery proceedings, in progress with respect to banking law offenses under sections 981, 1008, 1032, and 3322(d) of title 18 and and conspiracies to commit any such offense, including inactive investigations of such offenses;section 1833a of title 12","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fa%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a/1/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"investigations, prosecutions, and related proceedings described in subparagraph (A) which are inactive as of the close of the reporting period but have not been closed or declined; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a/1/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fa%2F1%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"unaddressed referrals which allege criminal misconduct involving offenses described in subparagraph (A),","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fa%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the nature and number of such matters closed, settled, or litigated to conclusion; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a/1/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fa%2F1%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the results achieved, including convictions and pretrial diversions, fines and penalties levied, restitution assessed and collected, and damages recovered, in such matters.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Analysis and report","label":"2 Analysis and report","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Attorney General shall analyze and report to the Congress on the data described in paragraph (1) and its coordination and other related activities named in section 41501(c)(2) of this title and shall provide such report on the data monthly through , and quarterly after such date.1So in original. Probably should be “41501(c)(3)”.1December 31, 1991","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Specifics of report","label":"b Specifics of report","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"categorize data as to various types of financial institutions and appropriate dollar loss categories;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"disclose data for each Federal judicial district;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"describe the activities of the Financial Institution Fraud Unit; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b/4/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fb%2F4%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the number of institutions, categorized by failed and open institutions, in which evidence of significant fraud, unlawful activity, insider abuse or serious misconduct has been alleged or detected;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b/4/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fb%2F4%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"civil, criminal, and administrative enforcement actions, including those of the Federal financial institutions regulatory agencies, brought against offenders;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b/4/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fb%2F4%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any settlements or judgments obtained against offenders;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b/4/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fb%2F4%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"indictments, guilty pleas, or verdicts obtained against offenders; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b/4/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t34/s41306/b/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft34%2Fs41306%2Fb%2F4%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the resources allocated in pursuit of investigations, prosecutions, and sentencings (including indictments, guilty pleas, or verdicts obtained against offenders) and related proceedings.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}
